items.description:
This is the LyCORIS version of the previously released LoRA version. While using the same dataset it generally performs better yielding higher quality output while being more flexible with outfits.

How to use
Just prompt away. The dataset is based on official character art with "simple background" and "white background" so use those tags if you want to strengthen the style further. You can also add standard tag for Disgaea (Senkai Makai Disgaea) to further change the style from the softer official character art towards the more "pointy" version provided the model has data on it.
Other things to try for AOM2 is using "3D" and "realistic" as negative tags though that shouldn't be necessary normally.
For more prompt suggestions see the sample images or the zip of training tags.

Note also that the end results depend on the sampler used, some producing more clean and polished results and others more close to drawings, experiment to see what works best with your model and goals.

While it's possible to prompt some characters from the game through tags, especially if you use their name too, there are now specialized LoRAs here on CivitAI for most of them if you want the best accuracy üòä

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!

Misc
Trained on NAI at 512 with 165 images at 512 resolution. Sample images from AOM2_NSFW
All images are untouched txt2img upscaled, no inpainting or helper embeddings used for quality transparence, e.g. - things should look even better if you do.

items.name: Mangaz B&W (Naruto and Dbz-eddiemauro)
items.description:
Before to use

  • You have to know how works Stable Diffusion. I recommend using Automatic1111 like an interface to launch the model.

  • This is a model trained on SD 1.5 model, so you have to consider that it is not perfect. I have to make so much testing before to arrive to a stable generation. I will enhance the model when a better base model arrives (like SD XL new one).

  • This is a LORA model, so it is recommended to use like an extension of a Checkpoint. I recommend you to use realistic dataset models.

  • I recommend you to follow me on my instagram account, where I will explain about AI image generation: https://www.instagram.com/eddiemauro.design/

Intro

MANGAZ B&W (NarutoDbz-eddiemauro) LORA: Hi, I‚Äôm a product and car designer, and I‚Äôm so excited to test with AI, I think is a good tool for designing. This tool (Lora) is for just fun. I was looking for a manga grayscale style that I can use for experimentation and also train learning. I was testing with multiple concepts with similar characteristics, so I decided to go with 2 of my favorites' anime: Naruto and Dragon Ball, so you can create images with those styles.

If you want to support my work and help me to upload more models (with better quality), you can do it by entering here and donating, I would greatly appreciate it: https://ko-fi.com/eddiemauro

Installation

  • I use Automatic1111, the best UI for Stable Diffusion image generation, so I recommend you to install locally or use it online with some Colab or other hosting. You can find online instructions or videos to do that. If you are going to install locally, you can watch this tutorial online and I recommend you to have at least a 6-8 Gb of VRAM Graphic Card (nvidia) to have a stable interface and launch with ‚ÄúMicrosoft Edge‚Äù because you will have problems on ‚ÄúGoogle Chrome‚Äù. Try also to install ‚Äúmedvram‚Äù or ‚Äúlowvram‚Äù options besides ‚Äúxformers‚Äù (search online how to).

  • This is a Lora model. You can watch this video to know how to install it. It is just to download a file and put it inside Lora file models. The Lora file extension is ‚Äú.safetensor‚Äù, and mostly the size is lower than a Checkpoint (that could be more than a gigabit).

  • You have to install also a Checkpoint model to use with, select one focused on realism visualization or 3D/render aspect.

  • Please for image creation you have to follow all my recommendations, if you don't, it is impossible to generate a good image quality. Also, you have to consider that from today AI image generation is not so consistent and perfect, you have to invest time to get it and make plenty of tests.

Recommendations for image generation

  • Checkpoint best models: ¬†SD 1.5 based models. It is mandatory to use with a checkpoint called "Fresh Draw v1" (for naruto style) and "Anylora" (for dbz style), so download first, install and load inside SD UI.¬†

  • Activation token/caption: Inside prompt space, the first word has to be: ‚Äúemangaz‚Äù and then put a second one depending on which style you would like to create: ‚Äúshippuden‚Äù to activate the naruto style, or "dbz" for Dragon Ball. It is mandatory, if you don't do it, it will not work properly.

  • Another recommended prompting: Inside prompt you can use those words that will enhance the image generation: in the positive space, "((monochrome)), grayscale, 8k, ((masterpiece)), HDR, professional" ; in the negative space: ‚Äú(worst quality:2), (low quality:2),, ((NSFW)), Cleavage, Pubic Hair, Nudity, Naked, Au naturel, Watermark, Text, censored, ((color)), jpeg artifacts, blurry, ((blind)), ((strabismus))‚Äù. You can also watch the image metadata of example images here and simulate the prompt. Also I recommend so prompt words to generate some character/image styles:

SHIPPUDEN

- Ninja: ninja, hairband (for ninja girl), forehead protector, kunai, cape, weapon, sword, sandals, weapon on back, konohagakure symbol

- Naruto: naruto, facial mark, forehead protector

- Girl: ponytail, long hair, short hair

- Kakashi: kakashi, ninja mask, forehead protector

- Sasuke: japanese clothes, spiked hair, black hair, cape

- Monsters (bijuu): kurama, monster, giant

DBZ

-Saiyan warrior: muscular, spiked hair, wristband, gloves, veins, super saiyan, saiyan armor

- Other: chinese clothes

ANY

-Simplier: simple background, white background,

- Battle scene: dirty

- Night scene: night sky

- Others: buildings, landscape, mountain, forest

- Shot: close-up, portrait, upper body, full body

  • Textual inversion/embedding or Lora tool recommended: I consider that ‚ÄúEasyNegative‚Äù is one best of textual inversion for negative prompt space, you should use it. Download here and install it, putting the file inside ‚Äúembeddings‚Äù. You can use it also ‚ÄúDetail Tweaker‚Äù to even reduce the details of the image, for that, you have to download from here, install like a Lora and use it inside positive prompt with a value of ‚Äú-0.5‚Äù. Use it when you realize the checkpoint used has so many details, but not when you see that minimalism is on it. This can change the shape of objects considerably.

  • Lora's weight: I'm trying to enhance the model, for now, this model works fine from 0.5 to 0.7. More than 0.8 will burn the shape and less than 0.4 will not take the style. Ideal is 0.6, but sometimes is better 0.5. It is interesting the results of less than 0.5.

  • VAE: it is recommended to use the ‚Äúkl-f8-anime2‚Äù. If you use a different one, it will generate a bit more realistic image.

  • Clip Skip: It was trained on 2, so use 2.

  • Steps and CFG: It is recommended to use Steps from ‚Äú25-35‚Äù and CFG scale from ‚Äú6-7‚Äù, the ideal is: steps 30, CFG 6. For next models, those values could change.

  • Sampler: Use DPM2a (strong style) y DPM++2Sa Karras (simplier, less details)(optionals:DPM2 Karras, DPM2a Karras). Make experimentation with other samplers if you like.

  • Batch: In txt2img try to put a value of 4 to generate more than 1 image and watch the generations. If you have a good graphic card, you can use ‚ÄúBatch size‚Äù, this will create at same time 4 images, increasing generation time; but if your computer cannot handle this, change to ‚ÄúBatch count‚Äù that will create 4 images in a row (not a same time), but generation time will be more.

  • Image aspect: Try to use these dimensions: 512x512, 768x512, 512x768, but even you can experiment with different. If you want to create a bigger image, use hires.fix in txt2img mode (mandatory if you want to generate a good image), img2img (it is better than hires) increase method or Ultimate SD Upscale script extension + ControlNet, or just upscaling with GAN models.

  • Create bigger images: There are 4 different methods to create large images in Stable Diffusion, you can check online how to. For first method ‚Äútxt2img hires.fix‚Äù, I recommend you to use upscale model called ‚ÄúR-ESRGAN 4x+Anime6B‚Äù. In hires.fix option put any ‚Äúupscale by‚Äù value, and then with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù of ‚Äú0.4‚Äù. For the second method, you have to select first the image generated in txt2img and then putting in img2img mode, increasing dimension at least ‚Äú1,5 times‚Äù with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù from ‚Äú0.3-0.5‚Äù. For the third method, you can use the same configuration of img2img, but activating ‚Äútile‚Äù mode of ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension and also the script of ‚ÄúUltimate SD Upscale‚Äù, but for that, I recommend you to watch a tutorial here. For the last method, you have to pass the generated image in txt2img to ‚Äúextras‚Äù and then select a GAN model and scale it, you can also use the ‚Äú4x-UltraSharp‚Äù model.

  • Get more control of your creation: Use ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension to generate a more controlled shape of what you want, and even you can test it with sketches. Use ‚ÄúScribble‚Äù or ‚ÄúLineart‚Äù modes. For that, I recommend you to install this extension and then learn to how to use. There are plenty of online videos about it.

  • Copy prompt for image metadata: You can download my example images here and put it inside ‚ÄúPNG info‚Äù tab from Automatic1111

Example Prompting:

Positive prompt:¬†

emangaz, shippuden, 1girl, ((monochrome)), grayscale, 8k, ((masterpiece)), HDR, professional <lora:emangaz2:0.7>

Negative prompt:¬†

Easynegative, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), ((NSFW)), Cleavage, Pubic Hair, Nudity, Naked, Au naturel, Watermark, Text, censored, ((color)), jpeg artifacts, blurry, ((blind)), ((strabismus))

Steps: from 30-35 (DPM2a (strong style) y DPM++2Sa Karras (simplier, less details)(optionals:DPM2 Karras, DPM2a Karras) )

CFG scale: 6-7 (6 Ideal).

What comes for the future

I‚Äôm already trying to enhance the model. If you like a better model of this version, try to keep supporting me on ko-fi, if there are more people supporting me, I can invest more time to train and enhance models, but if this doesn't happen I cannot.¬†

I launched my first private model for my Ko-fi membership lv.1, called "eddiemauro scene" minimalistic scenery creation for rendering. If you want to access to private models, you can support me and subscribe to this membership. I will also start to upload here more models centered on product and car design.


License

Watch here a Stable Diffusion license link. In the case of this specific model, use it for whatever you want in terms of image generation. It is prohibited:

  • Upload this model to any server or public online site without my permission.

  • Share online this model without my permission, using my exact model with a different name or uploading this model and then run it on services that generate images for money.

  • Merge it with a checkpoint or a Lora, and then publish it or share online, just talk to me first. In the future,

  • Sell this model or merges using this model.


Supporting

You can follow me on my social networks. I will show my process and also design tips and tools. Also, you can check my webpage and in case of you need a design service, I work like a freelance.

http://eddiemauro.design/

What I'm trying to say is: I did my best, but this has shortcomings.

Regardless, I hope you enjoy it!

items.name: Custome / Outfit Designer (Tool) by YeiyeiArt (COMISSIONS OPEN)
items.description:
REMEMBER to follow the social networks and ask for your own model. Hello everyone. I bring you something I've been working on this week, and I believe you will like it. It's a character costume designer. Sometimes, we have a character, but we wonder how they would look in different outfits. With this model, you can easily and quickly answer that question. Use the model with a strength of <1.0 - 0.8> to get better results. Use the activation word "(MoreOutfits:1.5)" for greater precision. Now, I'll explain how to get the best results based on my experience. So here's a small GUIDE:

  1. Use any 2D anime model you like. i used GalenaRedux.

  2. Use the following prompt to generate the layout correctly: "1girl, (MoreOutfits:1.5), (clothes variation, multiple views:1), (3views), full body, (skirt, shirt), curvy, looking at viewer, smile, :D, cute pose, (dynamic_pose:1.2), wide shot, (white background:1), (masterpiece:1.2), (best quality, highest quality), (ultra detailed), (8k, 4k, intricate), detailed eyes."

  3. I recommend using the "MoreDetails" embedding with a strength of <0.3> to improve the overall composition's details.

  4. Use the "ADetailed" extension and use any face model to enhance the characters' faces and correct any lack of detail in the eyes.

  5. Leave the clothing prompt empty; this will generate multiple character outfit options. If you use a specific clothing word, you can expect results with that particular garment.

  6. You can use generic clothing style tags to get outfits of that style, for example: (Cyberpunk, Pirate, etc.).

  7. Use a resolution of 512 x 512; this resolution generates the best results as the model was trained with those dimensions.

  8. You can use character LoRas and combine them with this model to see more outfits for that character (it's a lot of fun). Preferably, set your character models with a strength of <0.55 - 0.5> for better compatibility.

  9. Once you create the image, you can enhance the missing resolution with "Extras" and use an upscaler. I recommend R-ESRGAN 4+Anime.

items.name: Baldur's Gate 3 Item Icons LoRA
items.description:
Baldur's Gate 3 Item Icons LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon üÖøÔ∏è or feel free to buy me a coffee ‚òï

Intended as a resource for Baldur's Gate 3 Modders.
It can help converting gear screens into the right artstyle using img2img, and also generate item and jewelry icons from scratch. It can generate armor and weapon icons from scratch too, but they won't match the in game models unless you generate them with img2img.

Trained on DreamShaper 7, triggers with bg3 item icon. The other tags are taken from the icon names you find in Game.pak, meaning you can easily refer to those names to make your own. I trained the model to make green background consistently if prompted. This way it's easy to remove and make it transparent (requires a bit of skill, but I can't make SD generate with transparent background, so this is the best option I could find).

Should work around weight 1 on DreamShaper 7.

Lowering the lora weight will reduce the transparency effect, making it easier to clean the green background if you don't know how to deal with transparency.


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Jason Aldean (Small Town Expert) - Dreambooth Model (for likeness quality aficionados) - "JasonAldean Person" to trigger
items.description:
High Quality Dreambooth (JP's repo) trained model of country music sensation Jason Aldean. Created using recent hi-resolution images of the star.

Trigger with "JasonAldean Person" (yes, put person also). My suggestion is to use "Euler A" as the sampler. Use "Hi-Res fix" with the settings you'd normally use for best results. Use prompt weighting and/or Controlnet to get maximum flexibility out of this likeness model.

Trained locally using JP's repo (24gb VRAM req / arguably the best for likenesses).

Why do I post full checkpoints/models for 1 subject? Simply because the trained checkpoint gives you the best quality to start w/. LoRAs are fantastic for lots of things, but for human likenesses they don't match up to Dreambooth. It's easy to extract a LoRA from an SD checkpoint on your own if you prefer a LoRA for your workflow. For instance you can use the Auto1111 extension "Supermerger" to extract a LoRA. That said, LoRA will not match the quality of the original Dreambooth model (loss incurred).

Samples were mostly generated w/ Controlnet for initial guidance so you won't be able to replicate them with just the metadata (don't think Civitai lists whether or not CN was used).

items.name: Number Suit (Mahou Shoujo Lyrical Nanoha)
items.description:
My first attempt at making a Lora, done through the aid of this wonderful guide: https://civitai.com/models/22530/guide-make-your-own-loras-easy-and-free

As a massive fan of both the Nanoha series and the Numbers, I've been wanting to do something with their uniform for the longest time.

I have also made use of this Lyco: https://civitai.com/models/32108/numbers-uniform-magical-girl-lyrical-nanoha

I however found that it didn't always produce the results I was looking for. Thus I decided to see if I could make something myself. It's by no means perfect, but I have found myself able to more consistently get the look I'm trying to go for with this.

Recommended parameters:

Weight: I myself adhere to somewhere between 0.9 and 1.1. All depending on other prompts, lora's and models.

Base trigger: numbersuit

Additional:

yellow eyes, glowing eyes, intricate iris, eyeball, eye focus - For the most iconic Number look, feel free to experiment with leaving out everything aside from 'yellow eyes', but I found what I list to work best for me.

two-tone bodysuit:0.9, blue bodysuit:0.9, light blue bodysuit:0.9 - It can be a bit fickle with coloration, on bare bones prompts I find that this isn't necessary, bit helps when going a bit further down into use of other lora's.

No specific advise on model or VAE as I've found it to work decently with most of what I've tested, I can only advise experimenting. Though I do generally stick to Clip Skip 2.

I generally also recommend taking a gaze at the added images for further prompts I have used to get the results shown.

Training data:

Trained with AnyLora on about 71 images.

items.name: RPGGhost
items.description:
This LoRA is to create GHOSTS for medieval rpgs. I purposefully created this as more of a haunting style ghost. I think doubling up on the transparent and blurry tokens definitely help that style, but it was trained with a bunch of 1kx1k images that were aimed at this style.

The images were created with hires.fx x2, denoising 0.21, 4x_foolhardy_Remacri upscaler

The trigger words for this model are the following:

barefoot, black hair, blurry, face, from behind, ghost, long hair, looking at viewer, sitting, solo, standing, transparent, veil, very long hair, walking, white dress, white hair

items.name: Fortune (Subverse) LoRA
items.description:
The hacker and vigilante-for-hire Fortune from the game Subverse by Studio FOW. Works best on 0.6-1.0. Training done on NAI.

Trigger: "fortunesub" always needed "blue eyes, freckles, eyeliner" for consistency.

Suggestions:

  • Eyes: "Blue eyes, glowing eyes" can bring a pop to her eyes like in-game.

  • "sbjp, bodysuit, blue jacker" for her main outfit keep the weight at 1.0 when prompting this one.

  • Lower weight to 0.6-0.9 if prompting for other clothes but not needed since she is flexible.

  • "short hair, two-tone hair, pale skin" can help if those parts are being off.

  • There is light bleeding from the main outfit but its creates interesting looks for other generic clothing.

The main outfit is as accurate as I could get it with the limited data. I went the extra mile by hand editing data to try and teach the outfit but there are still inconsistencies due to the many details. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.name: Futura Hannah
items.description:
My rating vs expectation: 90%

(Very high quality dataset. Angles of the photos could be improved, which led to less than great likeness. Or perhaps it's still under-trained even at 472 epochs. Bummer it didn't turn out perfect. Also it's highly baked, so not very flexible with simple prompts.)

All TIs I make depict real adults. Please apply it with good judgement. If you're the model and want this removed reach out to me via link below. I welcome all criticisms and suggestions with curiosity. If you like my work, buy me a house:
https://ko-fi.com/futurafree

Experimenting with high step count, larger dataset and low learning rate and I'm having a bit more success with it. This TI was trained in sd1.5 base with 5 vectors, 52 images, 24525 steps, and 472 epochs. This was finetuned for epiCRealism evo3 and Realistic Vision V4.0, but may work on others.

TIPS:

  • MUST be the first word in the prompt for likeness and consistency.

    • Example: futurahannah24525v5, portrait of a woman, long dress etc.

    • Not: Portrait of futurahannah24525v5, etc.

  • Recommended strength:

    • (0.98-1.0)

  • I use adetailer for all images, with mediapipe_face_full, blank pos and neg, 1024x1024, inpaint mask blur: 20, inpaint noise strength: 0.45.

  • Again, prompt in adetailer is left blank most of the time; (*exception*: if Loras/Lycoris is used and has significant impact on the appearance of the model's face, copy paste pos prompt without Loras/Lycoris into adetailer).

  • Upscaler I use: 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k.
